column1: Information about each variable in the main_raw.csv is outlined in Row 2 of that dataset.
To see the exact text and coding options for each variable, you can open materials/codingForm_main.pdf
anova_raw.csv contains a subset of the variable from main_raw.csv
main_clean.csv contains a few additional variable that are calculated from the values in main_raw.csv
Variables ending in "_binary" are simply a yes/no as to whether the sample size calculation in question included information on that variable (1=yes;0=no)
Variable starting with "just_" are simply a decomposition of the "justification" variable (which had 7 options), into binary variable for each individual option
"all6" outlines how many of the six elements of the sample size calculation were provided
